  • Classes in com.vangav.backend.push_notifications.android used by com.vangav.backend.push_notifications.android 
    Class and Description
    AndroidNotification
    AndroidNotification class represents an Android Push Notification to be sent to Android devices through Google Cloud Messaging servers Serializable to be embedded into a JSON object and dispatched to a worker instance if needed Built on top of Google's gcm library --> https://github.com/google/gcm/tree/master/client-libraries/java/ rest-client/src/com/google/android/gcm/server
    AndroidNotificationProperties
    OPTIONAL AndroidNotificationProperties In the common case of a backend for one application, this properties file is a handy way to skip instantiating an AndroidNotificationSender and use the singleton instance instead which uses values from this properties file NOTE: values must be defined in the .prop file, default values are invalid values in that case of AndroidNotificationProperties
    AndroidNotificationSender
    AndroidNotificationSender handles sending AndroidNotification Objects to Android devices through Google Cloud Messaging Server Handles one app per instance Built on top of Google's gcm library --> https://github.com/google/gcm/tree/master/client-libraries/java/ rest-client/src/com/google/android/gcm/server
